# Trivy config-scan ignores — each is an INTENTIONAL, documented grant, not a regression.
#
# The deployer Role (k8s/bootstrap/deployer-rbac.yaml) is the least-privilege identity the CI runner
# deploys as. Its grants are scoped to exactly what `helm upgrade` does, and that file carries the full
# rationale ("THE SECRETS TRADE"). These two checks flag precisely those required grants:
#
#   AVD-KSV-0053  Role has pods/exec. `helm --wait` watches Pods and the version-writer hook Job
#                 spawns one; the deploy cannot wait on a rollout without it.
#   AVD-KSV-0056  Role can write services/endpoints/ingresses. helm server-side-applies the chart's
#                 Services and Ingress on every upgrade, so it must. It still cannot touch Roles,
#                 RoleBindings, ServiceAccounts or SealedSecrets — those stay bootstrap-only.
#
# Removing either breaks deploys. This is a single-developer platform on one trusted machine, where
# the escalation these checks guard against (a shared or hosted runner exfiltrating via exec) does not
# apply. Scoped to the deployer Role by intent; no workload manifest trips these.
AVD-KSV-0053
AVD-KSV-0056
